properties.name: Antalya, Turkey, AYT
properties.description: Posted by Elomba Stayed at a luxury hotel, drank the brau and tuborg all day in the sun. I did fall into a land mine shaft on a undeveloped piece of land behind the Hilton. Still have the scar to prove it.

properties.name: Athens, Greece
properties.description: Posted by Elomba Athens, GreeceAthens Greece, nice architecture, beautiful scenery, great night life as well. Austrialian bartendar from the Hard Rock made me a tornado shot, it was green but swirled in your mouth when drink it.

properties.name: Cannes, France
properties.description: Posted by Elomba  Spent a couple weeks in Cannes France, not during the movie festival, but we did get to experience America\'s independence day in another country. Awesome time.

properties.name: Dubai, United Arab Emirates
properties.description: Posted by Elomba Probably the most dangerous and most westernized country I\'ve been to. Absolutely nothing to write home about, sand, fancy cars, big buildings and sheiks. Not fun.

properties.name: Haifi Israel
properties.description: Posted by Elomba Awesome place! Locals love americans, found a great bar that plays rock music in a hill on the edge of a park located in the middle of the city.

properties.name: Jacksonville
properties.description: Posted by Elomba Jacksonville, FLCalled it home for 4 years. Club 5, Milk Bar, Mr. McGoos, Doll House, the beach nuff said.

properties.description: Posted by Elomba What can you say? The holy land, the church of sepulchre, the stone they laid jesus on, completely historical. Great trip.

properties.name: Marseille, France
properties.description: Posted by Elomba Marseille, FranceMarseille, stayed at the Mercure (sp) hotel drank imported J&B Whiskey and terrorized the locals. Also went sight seeing. Not much to write home about.

properties.name: Naples, Italy
properties.description: Posted by Elomba Company picnic in the park located inside an inactive volcano. Not bad - lot\'s of military.

properties.name: Palma de mallorca (Spain)
properties.description: Posted by Elomba Great beach, great night life. This place is awesome. Locals tend to stay away, but there are plenty of other folks on vacation/holiday to have fun with and I sure did take advantage of that.

properties.name: Portsmouth
properties.description: Posted by Elomba Portsmouth, EnglandNot much to do here. However, Stonehenge is nearby so that\'s pretty exciting. Did experience my first true Guinness here, and after two I was walking and talking funny. The locals are great.
